subSubSection.paragraph:
METASOMA AND TELSON (
Figs. 18 and 19
): The metasoma is sparsely hirsute and finely granulated, with sparse, relatively large granules. The first segment bears 10 carinae, the second to fourth segments bear eight carinae, and the fifth segment bears seven carinae. The dorsolateral carinae of the third and fourth segments posteriorly terminate in a pronounced denticle. The telson is elongate, without granules.
